\citation{TODO-diffusion-forcing}
\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {1}{\ignorespaces Our method. Standard conditional training pastes in clean conditioning tokens, covering only the top edge ($t'{=}1$) of the training space (orange). Instead, we train over a range of conditioning noise levels (blue region), exposing the model to a curriculum of conditioning strengths. At generation time we still integrate the response from noise ($t{=}0$) to clean ($t{=}1$) with the conditioning held clean.}}{3}{figure.1}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:method}{{1}{3}{Our method. Standard conditional training pastes in clean conditioning tokens, covering only the top edge ($t'{=}1$) of the training space (orange). Instead, we train over a range of conditioning noise levels (blue region), exposing the model to a curriculum of conditioning strengths. At generation time we still integrate the response from noise ($t{=}0$) to clean ($t{=}1$) with the conditioning held clean}{figure.1}{}}
